---
description: CareerFlow engineering principles
alwaysApply: true
---

CareerFlow prioritizes production-style architecture over academic complexity.

Follow these principles:

- Backend-first engineering.
- Readability over cleverness.
- Explicit code over framework magic.
- Thin controllers.
- Business logic belongs in services.
- Repository layer only performs persistence.
- One microservice owns one database.
- JWT subject (sub) is the ownership boundary.
- Never trust user IDs supplied by clients.
- Prefer value objects over unnecessary entities.
- Avoid bidirectional JPA relationships.
- Flyway owns schema evolution.
- Hibernate validates schemas only.
- Feature-based packaging.
- Constructor injection only.
- DTOs for all API boundaries.
- Use UTC timestamps.
- Use BigDecimal for monetary values.
- Avoid unnecessary abstractions.
- Optimize for maintainability rather than cleverness.

When multiple designs are possible, recommend the simplest production-quality solution.